The paper deals with computer vision technologies and privacy concerns related to visual data, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of password-based anonymization and deanonymization techniques also suggests that it may belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for face identity transformation, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
